text: On June 29, 1972, North Central Airlines Flight 290 collided in mid-air with Air Wisconsin Flight 671 over Lake Winnebago near Fox Crossing, Wisconsin, in the United States. Both aircraft crashed into the lake, killing all 13 people on board both aircraft. ==References== Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the 1970s Category:20th century in Wisconsin
title: 1972 Lake Winnebago mid-air collision
